    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert QA Lead. Your task is to analyze a Jira bug report and extract/generate three specific fields for a summary report: Description, Type, and Area.\n\nAnalyze the following inputs:\n- Summary (Title): {{ $json['Bugs Name'] }}\n- Description (Raw): {{ $json.Desctiption }}\n\nStrictly follow these rules for extraction:\n1. \"Description\": Rewrite the raw description into a single, clear, and professional paragraph (3-4 sentences max). Focus only on the core issue. Remove logs, steps, and clutter.\n2. \"Type\": Classify the bug category. Choose strictly from: \"Functional\", \"UI/UX\", \"Performance\", or \"Security\". (e.g., if it's a layout/text issue -> \"UI/UX\", if it's a broken feature/calculation -> \"Functional\").\n3. \"Area\": Identify where the bug occurs. Look at the Summary first — if there is a module name in brackets at the beginning (like \"[Deals]\" or \"[Agents]\"), extract that word without brackets. If there are no brackets, analyze the context and specify the system module name (e.g., \"Viewing event\", \"Client form\", \"Analytics\").\n\nOutput MUST be strictly in English and formatted as a raw JSON object with keys \"description\", \"type\", and \"area\". Do not include any markdown formatting like ```json.\n\nExample output format:\n{\n  \"description\": \"When creating a new Viewing event, the user cannot interact with the modal form because clicks trigger elements behind it.\",\n  \"type\": \"Functional\",\n  \"area\": \"Viewing event\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
